    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rubber boot from the gear shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the assembly in a vise with the large opening up.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gear shift lever tension spring by twisting a heavy screwdriver between the
                    spring and housing, forcing the spring from its seat under the lugs cast in the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302458">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302458" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302458" filename="../figg13/g1302458.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Remove Gear Shift Lever Tension Spring</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring from the housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring washer and gear shift lever out through the bottom of the
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302459">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302459" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302459" filename="../figg13/g1302459.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Remove Tension Spring Washer and Gear Shift Lever</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut and lockwasher from the gear shift lever pivot pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pivot pin by forcing it inward and through the wall of the housing.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
